  "prompt": "What is the most underrated problem in the life of a musician?",
  "response": "There are several underrated challenges musicians face, but one often overlooked issue is the mental health strain from constant rejection, inconsistent income, and career uncertainty. Musicians frequently experience:\n\n1. High levels of performance anxiety\n2. Financial instability\n3. Self-doubt and imposter syndrome\n4. Irregular work schedules\n5. Pressure to constantly create and perform\n6. Difficulty maintaining personal relationships\n7. Burnout from balancing creativity with business demands\n8. Limited job security\n9. Emotional vulnerability from public criticism\n10. Complex work-life balance\n\nWhile many see the glamorous side of music, the psychological toll and consistent emotional labor are rarely discussed.\n\nWould you be interested in hearing more about any of these challenges?",
